      <hedline>
        <hl1>Rules of the Game</hl1>
      </hedline>
      <abstract>
        <p>Harold Freeman letter on Jonathan Reynolds' April 30 article recalls his own favorite English delicacies2</p>
      </abstract>
    </body.head>
    <body.content>
      <block class="lead_paragraph">
        <p>As a London-born ex-Brit, I was delighted to be reminded of such delicacies as Kate-and-Sidney (steak-and-kidney) pie, Stilton cheese and treacle pudding. The mere mention of such foods was sufficient to get my salivary glands working overtime.</p>
        <p>Harold Freeman</p>
        <p>Coram, N.Y.</p>
      </block>
